intro: Trachymene kochii, commonly known as the mountain trachymene, is a flowering plant native to Australia. It belongs to the familyApiaceae, which includes caraway and parsley. The plant is characterized by its slender, erect stems and small, greenish-white flowers arranged in umbels. Its leaves are pinnately divided, giving it a feathery appearance. Trachymene kochii typically grows in rocky or sandy soils in open woodland and heathland environments.
